<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
A common and widespread species of the subantarctic forests and moorlands of the Magallanes and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aisén">Aisen</normalizedToken>
Regions on damp to wet soil, fallen logs, and tree stumps (
<bibRefCitation author="Ochi, H" journalOrPublisher="Nature and Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="11 - 47" refId="B18" refString="Ochi, H, 1982. A revision of the Bryoideae (Musci) in southern South America. Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University. Nature and Science 31: 11 - 47" title="A revision of the Bryoideae (Musci) in southern South America. Journal of the Faculty of Education, Tottori University." volume="31" year="1982">Ochi 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Reports from further north are likely misidentifications and are either 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. andicola" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="andicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. andicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is a robust species with dioicous sexual condition, rosulate stems, sometimes with 2+ interrupted clumps along stems, large leaves that are contorted to somewhat imbricate when dry, serrulate distal leaf margins, an extremely wide limbidium of 4+ rows distally, and brown to red-brown rhizoidal tubers. The wide limbidium often gives the leaves a white-margined appearance. The species is also found in Argentina, the Falkland Islands, and extreme southern New Zealand (Illustrations: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" author="Mohamed, MA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bryology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="401 - 465" refId="B12" refString="Mohamed, MA, 1979. A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species. Journal of Bryology 10 (4): 401 - 465, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" title="A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" volume="10" year="1979">Mohamed 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 422, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cardot" authorityYear="1905" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum perlimbatum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perlimbatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Bryum perlimbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fife, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" publicationUrl="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" refId="B4" refString="Fife, AJ, 2015. Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N.Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at: https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" title="Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N. Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at:" url="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" year="2015">Fife 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 87, as 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. perlimbatum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perlimbatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. perlimbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
